WEBVTT

00:07.179 --> 00:09.285
- [News Anchor] Alexander
Litvinenko has died.

00:09.285 --> 00:11.183
But who or what killed him?

00:11.183 --> 00:13.703
Our security correspondent
is Gordon Carrera.

00:13.703 --> 00:15.463
- [Gordon]
Unfortunately, his death

00:15.463 --> 00:17.638
doesn't necessarily
bring us any closer

00:17.638 --> 00:19.329
to know what killed him.

00:19.329 --> 00:21.159
University College
Hospital said last night

00:21.159 --> 00:22.539
that he died at about 9:21

00:22.539 --> 00:24.783
and the medical team
did everything possible.

00:24.783 --> 00:27.027
They said, it's now in the
hands of Scotland Yard.

00:27.027 --> 00:28.131
- I'll do the talking.

00:33.999 --> 00:38.107
[people speaking indistinctly]

00:38.107 --> 00:39.936
And in fact, we
have confirmation

00:39.936 --> 00:41.731
that it was Polonium
that killed your husband,

00:41.731 --> 00:44.320
Mrs. Litvinenko,
that is a good thing.

00:44.320 --> 00:46.908
It means we can officially
investigate this

00:46.908 --> 00:48.979
as a suspicious death.

00:51.085 --> 00:52.707
- No.

00:52.707 --> 00:53.984
- [Clive] Sorry?

00:53.984 --> 00:55.745
- Not suspicious death,

00:56.953 --> 00:57.747
murder.

00:58.989 --> 01:00.819
Sasha was murdered.

01:00.819 --> 01:03.201
- [Clive] That may well
turn out to be the case.

01:03.201 --> 01:04.133
But for now.

01:04.133 --> 01:05.410
- He tell you what happened.

01:06.756 --> 01:07.688
He tell.

01:07.688 --> 01:10.518
[speaks in foreign language]

01:10.518 --> 01:12.348
- He told us lots of things,

01:12.348 --> 01:14.419
all of them extremely valuable.

01:14.419 --> 01:19.044
And his interviews
are our guide now.

01:20.114 --> 01:22.910
But we must be as thorough

01:23.842 --> 01:26.845
in interrogating his account

01:26.845 --> 01:28.329
as he was in giving it.

01:29.779 --> 01:33.472
It may also be that we have
to ask you to leave your home

01:33.472 --> 01:37.131
just for a time so we
can test for Polonium.

01:37.131 --> 01:38.512
- They've been here
for a month already.

01:38.512 --> 01:40.376
- I'm sure you understand.

01:40.376 --> 01:41.825
- [Duncan] There are places

01:41.825 --> 01:42.895
that we can make available
to you for these.

01:42.895 --> 01:44.656
- No, no, no, thank you.

01:44.656 --> 01:46.071
It can all be taken care of.

01:48.073 --> 01:53.043
- Now you'll have two family
liaison officers appointed.

01:54.390 --> 01:57.876
Ray with the beard
there, he's a vegetarian.

01:57.876 --> 02:01.397
And Aiden, he's an ex para,
who's frightened of spiders.

02:01.397 --> 02:02.915
Not that you heard it from me.

02:06.712 --> 02:07.541
- That's it?

02:10.889 --> 02:14.548
You go just like this?

02:14.548 --> 02:17.067
- I'm not gonna hang around to
offer you emotional support.

02:17.067 --> 02:18.310
That's their job.

02:18.310 --> 02:20.554
Mine is to find out who
did this to your husband

02:22.003 --> 02:23.488
and make sure justice is done.

02:29.873 --> 02:30.702
- Detective.

02:31.634 --> 02:33.877
[gentle music]

02:33.877 --> 02:34.844
Thank you.

02:34.844 --> 02:36.466
[gentle music]

02:36.466 --> 02:39.987
- Please, Mrs.
Litvinenko, not yet.

02:39.987 --> 02:42.748
[dramatic music]

02:49.169 --> 02:51.723
[car engines revving]

02:51.723 --> 02:54.381
- [Pat] I mean, one microgram
of this stuff is fatal.

02:54.381 --> 02:55.347
- Microgram?

02:55.347 --> 02:56.935
- About half a grain of sand.

02:56.935 --> 03:00.559
So in answer to your
next question, thousands,

03:00.559 --> 03:02.527
thousands, possibly
tens of thousands

03:02.527 --> 03:04.701
of lives are in danger here.

03:04.701 --> 03:06.600
I mean it's no
exaggeration to say

03:06.600 --> 03:09.292
that this is a chemical
attack on the United Kingdom.

03:10.811 --> 03:12.053
- Home Secretary.

03:12.053 --> 03:13.572
I know there are people
in this room are keen

03:13.572 --> 03:15.850
to get going on
a murder inquiry.

03:15.850 --> 03:17.197
It's our recommendation

03:17.197 --> 03:19.026
that this is a public
health issue first,

03:19.026 --> 03:20.648
a police matter, second.

03:20.648 --> 03:21.994
- We're sealing off any areas

03:21.994 --> 03:24.204
thought to be contaminated
with Polonium.

03:24.204 --> 03:26.792
That's already happened at
the hospital and the hotel.

03:26.792 --> 03:28.553
- And the sushi place.

03:28.553 --> 03:30.658
- [Pat] Then if we know
what are the sites to check,

03:30.658 --> 03:32.315
we can get a good idea of
how containable this is.

03:32.315 --> 03:35.007
- So it's not a public
health issue first, is it?

03:36.423 --> 03:37.803
- That's the recommendation.

03:37.803 --> 03:40.737
- Sure, but it won't
work like that.

03:40.737 --> 03:42.912
- We know how to
handle Polonium-210.

03:42.912 --> 03:46.122
- I agree, but you don't
know where to find it.

03:46.122 --> 03:47.641
Only last night we have
been told on the phone,

03:47.641 --> 03:49.919
this is the most dangerous
substance known to man,

03:49.919 --> 03:52.784
in this same breath is being
told it's impossible spot.

03:52.784 --> 03:54.303
Doesn't smell, doesn't
have any color,

03:54.303 --> 03:57.375
doesn't say good morning when
you come down for breakfast.

03:57.375 --> 03:58.928
[laughing]

03:58.928 --> 04:01.171
In order to get an handle on
the risk to public health,

04:01.171 --> 04:02.932
you have to know where it is.

04:02.932 --> 04:06.453
And you can't do that
without knowing who's had it

04:06.453 --> 04:07.764
and where they've been.

04:08.662 --> 04:11.320
Look, send us your teams.

04:12.769 --> 04:15.255
We'll identify the
sites that need checking

04:15.255 --> 04:16.635
so you can check them.

04:17.809 --> 04:20.743
And together we can
move forward on this.

04:20.743 --> 04:22.158
How's that sound?

04:22.158 --> 04:23.953
- [John] You don't
have a name card?

04:24.850 --> 04:26.266
- This is Clive Timmons,

04:26.266 --> 04:28.578
SIO on the Litvinenko
investigation.

04:32.064 --> 04:35.413
- And have you ever dealt with
a case like this, Detective?

04:36.276 --> 04:37.138
- Has anyone?

04:40.280 --> 04:44.284
[people speaking indistinctly]

04:45.871 --> 04:48.011
- [News Anchor] Because of
the fingers being pointed,

04:48.011 --> 04:51.843
not least by the victim
himself, at President Putin,

04:51.843 --> 04:54.535
is this likely to cause
a major diplomatic row?

04:54.535 --> 04:56.503
- [Simon] I think the
question is evidence.

04:56.503 --> 04:58.988
The efficiency, the
professionalism of this killing

04:58.988 --> 05:00.990
means precisely that
it may be very hard

05:00.990 --> 05:02.232
to find any evidence.

05:02.232 --> 05:03.303
- [News Anchor]
Simon, thank you.

05:03.303 --> 05:04.131
- Bloody hell.

05:05.063 --> 05:07.859
[dramatic music]

05:07.859 --> 05:11.000
- [Aiden] Thank you.

05:11.000 --> 05:12.519
- Thanks.

05:12.519 --> 05:16.212
- So you go to school
around here, Anatoly?

05:18.835 --> 05:22.356
- Anatoly's school
is City of London.

05:25.325 --> 05:28.466
[car engine revving]

05:30.985 --> 05:32.332
- Time to pack some things.

05:44.482 --> 05:48.417
[people speaking indistinctly]

05:59.359 --> 06:02.189
[birds chirping]

06:02.189 --> 06:06.124
[people speaking indistinctly]

06:15.305 --> 06:17.860
[gentle music]

06:27.490 --> 06:30.182
[Marina crying]

06:36.223 --> 06:38.294
- [Nurse] They're asking
we clear the area.

06:39.502 --> 06:42.712
Detective, we need to go.

06:42.712 --> 06:43.989
- Sorry.

06:43.989 --> 06:45.128
[dramatic music]

06:45.128 --> 06:46.785
[heart machine beeping]

06:46.785 --> 06:49.616
[dramatic music]

06:54.966 --> 06:57.175
- Somebody within
the United Kingdom

06:57.175 --> 07:00.489
has been deliberately poisoned
by a type of radiation.

07:01.386 --> 07:04.147
It's known as an alpha emitter.

07:04.147 --> 07:07.634
So if the water in this
glass were Polonium,

07:07.634 --> 07:09.394
no radiation would escape.

07:10.257 --> 07:13.260
No harm would come to me or you

07:13.260 --> 07:15.676
by being here in its presence.

07:15.676 --> 07:19.335
However, were we to
ingest a single particle,

07:19.335 --> 07:22.372
if we ate it, drank
it, inhaled it

07:22.372 --> 07:24.305
as it floated through the air

07:24.305 --> 07:27.619
or returned our body
through a cut or a wound,

07:27.619 --> 07:29.138
that would be fatal.

07:29.138 --> 07:31.347
- [Reporter] Would you say the
general public are at risk?

07:31.347 --> 07:33.901
- [Pat] That I'm
afraid we cannot say.

07:33.901 --> 07:36.732
[dramatic music]

07:44.843 --> 07:46.983
- So at any given site,

07:46.983 --> 07:49.434
a clean, dirty line.

07:51.056 --> 07:52.920
On one side you are clean

07:52.920 --> 07:56.199
and on the other side you are
in a contaminated environment.

07:56.199 --> 07:57.787
So it's up to the line.

07:59.375 --> 08:02.930
Outer garments off,
hazmat suits on.

08:10.835 --> 08:13.596
And then it is boots and gloves.

08:17.427 --> 08:18.808
Then tape at the ankle,

08:20.154 --> 08:21.224
under the wrist.

08:24.780 --> 08:29.578
Then it is mask and hood

08:29.578 --> 08:33.029
and zips, fully
zipped and zips taped.

08:35.445 --> 08:37.447
Then a colleague
double checks for you.

08:37.447 --> 08:38.966
And thank you, Michael.

08:38.966 --> 08:40.450
Only now do we cross the line,

08:40.450 --> 08:43.661
making sure we've
got one of these.

08:43.661 --> 08:45.732
This is an alpha detector.

08:46.629 --> 08:48.458
[dramatic music]

08:48.458 --> 08:51.151
So we enter the site as a team.

08:52.462 --> 08:56.812
We move as a team,
sweeping as a team.

08:56.812 --> 08:59.815
In the event of a positive
reading, however minimal,

08:59.815 --> 09:02.058
you notify the team
leader and you exit

09:02.058 --> 09:04.405
in the exact same way.

09:05.579 --> 09:07.477
Deviate from any part of that

09:07.477 --> 09:09.583
and you put your life

09:09.583 --> 09:12.586
and the lives of the people
standing next to you right now

09:13.483 --> 09:14.864
in danger.

09:14.864 --> 09:16.486
[dramatic music]

09:16.486 --> 09:18.661
- We'll repeat
that one more time.

09:18.661 --> 09:20.076
And then we'll get
the list of sites

09:20.076 --> 09:21.768
from Detective Timmons here.

09:24.011 --> 09:25.288
Thank you Michael.

09:25.288 --> 09:28.360
- [Scientist] So, hazmat
suit then it's boots.

09:30.121 --> 09:34.125
[people speaking indistinctly]

09:35.402 --> 09:38.094
- [Clive] If I ask my
lot to go out there,

09:38.094 --> 09:39.682
they're gonna ask
me what the risk is

09:39.682 --> 09:42.029
and I'm gonna tell
'em about that.

09:42.029 --> 09:44.031
- You certainly
don't tell 'em that.

09:44.031 --> 09:45.688
- I'm gonna have to.

09:46.862 --> 09:48.657
- You carry the worry for them.

09:50.037 --> 09:51.245
That's your job.

09:51.245 --> 09:54.248
Otherwise this whole
thing starts to unravel.

09:54.248 --> 09:59.081
And trust me, panic will
spread faster than the poison.

09:59.081 --> 10:02.429
[elevator bell ringing]

10:04.017 --> 10:08.642
[people speaking indistinctly]

10:08.642 --> 10:11.507
[dramatic music]

10:27.834 --> 10:30.181
- All right, boys and girls,

10:31.734 --> 10:34.806
the plan is as follows.

10:36.843 --> 10:39.949
We start with Litvinenko

10:39.949 --> 10:42.400
and we work
backwards from there.

10:44.091 --> 10:48.544
If there's Polonium
at the house, as we
think there will be,

10:49.614 --> 10:51.616
our next question is,

10:51.616 --> 10:53.549
where was he prior to that?

10:54.792 --> 10:55.620
We go there.

10:57.001 --> 10:58.588
If there's Polonium there too,

10:59.797 --> 11:00.729
we go back again.

11:02.109 --> 11:06.735
And we keep on checking
until we find where it stops.

11:08.564 --> 11:09.945
The place it first happened.

11:11.774 --> 11:15.744
We identify the person or
persons present at that place

11:16.814 --> 11:18.022
and we have our suspect.

11:19.644 --> 11:23.096
We follow the poison,
we find a poisoner.

11:23.096 --> 11:24.649
[all laughing]

11:24.649 --> 11:27.790
[police sirens blaring]

11:27.790 --> 11:29.896
Look, we'll take this on,

11:31.621 --> 11:34.107
not because we promise
the British citizen

11:34.107 --> 11:36.730
that's what we do,
although we have.

11:37.697 --> 11:39.595
Not because we got the backing

11:39.595 --> 11:42.840
of the best scientists in
the world, although we do.

11:45.705 --> 11:47.465
But because it's our duty.

11:49.122 --> 11:51.089
Yes, there are unknowables.

11:52.401 --> 11:54.437
But dealing with
unknowables is what you do.

11:54.437 --> 11:55.715
It's what you're good at.

11:55.715 --> 11:58.372
It's why I choose
you to work here.

11:58.372 --> 12:01.513
[dramatic music]

12:01.513 --> 12:02.963
That said,

12:02.963 --> 12:06.415
if there's anyone in this
room that doesn't fancy this,

12:07.657 --> 12:09.729
you're welcome to step away.

12:09.729 --> 12:10.868
[dramatic music]

12:10.868 --> 12:12.076
This is your chance.

12:13.525 --> 12:16.597
No judgment, no one will
hold anything against you.

12:16.597 --> 12:18.910
[dramatic music]

12:18.910 --> 12:20.325
You have to speak up now.

12:21.223 --> 12:24.053
[dramatic music]

12:26.953 --> 12:27.781
Right.

12:29.058 --> 12:30.853
Don't fuck this up.

12:30.853 --> 12:33.304
[dramatic music]

12:33.304 --> 12:36.169
[people speaking indistinctly]

12:36.169 --> 12:39.724
[dramatic music]

12:39.724 --> 12:43.659
[people speaking indistinctly]

12:44.867 --> 12:46.420
- [Reporter] Mrs. Litvinenko.

12:46.420 --> 12:50.355
[people speaking indistinctly]

12:53.117 --> 12:56.672
[camera shutters clicking]

12:57.915 --> 13:01.642
[helicopter blades whirring]

13:01.642 --> 13:05.543
[people speaking indistinctly]

13:06.751 --> 13:09.512
[dramatic music]

13:14.897 --> 13:18.004
[car engine revving]

13:19.557 --> 13:23.043
[helicopter blades whirring]

13:23.043 --> 13:26.633
[dramatic music]

13:26.633 --> 13:29.947
[alpha machine buzzing]

13:32.397 --> 13:35.124
[dramatic music]

13:40.060 --> 13:43.408
[alpha machine buzzing]

13:44.616 --> 13:47.447
[dramatic music]

13:58.941 --> 14:02.842
- [Litvinenko Voiceover]
I have pain in stomach.

14:02.842 --> 14:06.224
[alpha machine buzzing]

14:07.087 --> 14:09.158
Foam in mouth, I am sick.

14:11.195 --> 14:14.129
Been poisoned, I know this.

14:14.129 --> 14:16.165
[alpha machine beeping]

14:16.165 --> 14:17.718
- Yeah, this is good.

14:18.892 --> 14:20.238
- If we hadn't found
plenum at the house,

14:20.238 --> 14:21.170
it'd be something more.

14:21.170 --> 14:23.241
- That is what he told us.

14:23.241 --> 14:24.864
He takes us through
everything on these,

14:24.864 --> 14:27.763
including the stuff about
Scaramella, Lugovoi and Kovtun.

14:27.763 --> 14:29.454
He was adamant that
it was one of those.

14:29.454 --> 14:31.215
- We're gonna search everywhere,

14:31.215 --> 14:32.872
all the places he's been.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.459
Treating them all the same.

14:34.459 --> 14:35.357
- Even the motel?

14:35.357 --> 14:37.014
- [Clive] Everywhere.

14:37.014 --> 14:38.532
- You don't believe him?

14:38.532 --> 14:41.018
- I'm just not taking his
word for it, that's all.

14:41.018 --> 14:42.433
- Because he's ex KGB.

14:42.433 --> 14:44.400
- Because we never take
any one person's word

14:44.400 --> 14:45.470
for anything, do we?

14:46.678 --> 14:48.025
We check for ourselves.

14:49.129 --> 14:50.406
Test everything.

14:50.406 --> 14:52.477
Every one, which
includes the two of you.

14:52.477 --> 14:53.306
- Please.

14:54.617 --> 14:56.033
- You were with him the most.

14:57.620 --> 14:59.484
You'll need the all clear.

14:59.484 --> 15:01.521
I'm not having you
put a team in danger.

15:05.490 --> 15:08.562
[telephone ringing]

15:08.562 --> 15:09.770
- Scaramella.

15:09.770 --> 15:11.255
- Ah, you got him?

15:11.255 --> 15:12.635
- Well, he's back in Italy now,

15:12.635 --> 15:14.085
but he's a regular in London

15:14.085 --> 15:16.053
and he's definitely
got ties to Russia.

15:16.053 --> 15:17.951
- But we've got him as an
in intelligence analyst,

15:17.951 --> 15:20.989
he's big on nuclear energy in
the KGB's influence overseas.

15:20.989 --> 15:22.922
- So he anti KGB?

15:22.922 --> 15:23.888
- Well he might be.

15:23.888 --> 15:25.717
But then so was Litvinenko.

15:25.717 --> 15:28.686
So if you're trying to arrange
a lunch with Litvinenko.

15:28.686 --> 15:31.137
- Being anti KGB doesn't hurt.

15:31.137 --> 15:33.208
All right, let's find him.

15:33.208 --> 15:34.726
- What, as been me personally?

15:36.349 --> 15:37.384
- Is that all right Tubs?

15:37.384 --> 15:39.145
- Well, I'm not on this job gov.

15:39.145 --> 15:40.767
It's just a favor for Duncan.

15:40.767 --> 15:42.527
- Oh, what you doing?

15:42.527 --> 15:43.356
- Now?

15:44.495 --> 15:47.325
I'm waiting on feedback
on the report on 77.

15:47.325 --> 15:49.672
- Oh right, well
why you waiting.

15:50.708 --> 15:53.780
[people speaking indistinctly]

15:53.780 --> 15:54.954
- You're welcome Tubs.

15:54.954 --> 15:56.956
[gentle upbeat music]

15:56.956 --> 16:00.407
[speaking indistinctly]

16:01.753 --> 16:03.203
- [Reporter] Scotland
Yard detectors

16:03.203 --> 16:05.619
are tracing the final steps
of a former Russian spy.

16:05.619 --> 16:07.069
[police sirens blaring]

16:07.069 --> 16:09.278
He was poisoned by a rare
radioactive substance.

16:09.278 --> 16:10.210
[police sirens blaring]

16:10.210 --> 16:12.247
[people speaking indistinctly]

16:12.247 --> 16:15.043
- Manager's called
Martin Spencer.

16:15.043 --> 16:16.527
Says he has followed the
whole thing on the news

16:16.527 --> 16:17.735
since it started.

16:17.735 --> 16:19.909
Seems rather keen to help.

16:19.909 --> 16:20.980
- Oh, good.

16:20.980 --> 16:23.085
- Kovtun, yes, I remember.

16:23.085 --> 16:25.398
But he was quite a low-key guy.

16:25.398 --> 16:26.847
- Who kept himself to himself.

16:26.847 --> 16:28.090
- Exactly.

16:28.090 --> 16:31.024
But Lugovoi,

16:31.024 --> 16:34.062
Lugovoi walked around as
if he owned the place.

16:34.062 --> 16:35.166
- Arrogant.

16:35.166 --> 16:36.961
- In my view, yes.

16:36.961 --> 16:38.204
- And can you confirm

16:38.204 --> 16:40.068
they were here on the
dates we've given you?

16:41.414 --> 16:46.005
- Lugovoi, room
441, Kovtun, 382.

16:46.005 --> 16:47.972
- May we have that as
a printout, Martin?

16:47.972 --> 16:48.800
- Yep.

16:51.976 --> 16:56.291
Now there is no CCTV in
the Pine Bar, nothing.

16:57.878 --> 16:59.259
Who knows,

16:59.259 --> 17:00.847
maybe that's why they chose it.

17:02.642 --> 17:05.265
- And what about the
rest of the hotel?

17:05.265 --> 17:06.818
Do you still have
the CCTV for that?

17:06.818 --> 17:09.338
- Yeah, that of
course we can check.

17:09.338 --> 17:10.581
- Yeah, thank you Martin.

17:12.203 --> 17:13.411
- You want me to
do that right now?

17:13.411 --> 17:14.516
- Yes, please, Martin.

17:16.449 --> 17:18.520
- [Dr. Onome] And how
am I spelling Hyatt?

17:18.520 --> 17:22.903
- [Brent] Hotel Yankee
Alpha, Tango, Tango.

17:22.903 --> 17:23.732
- Thank you.

17:25.044 --> 17:26.873
Any nausea at all?

17:26.873 --> 17:28.150
Upset stomach?

17:28.150 --> 17:29.255
- No.

17:29.255 --> 17:31.291
- And how about your partner?

17:31.291 --> 17:33.086
- [Brent] She's fine, thanks.

17:33.086 --> 17:33.949
- Your children?

17:37.125 --> 17:38.678
Do you have children?

17:38.678 --> 17:40.956
- Well, we're hoping to.

17:43.200 --> 17:44.063
Will this,

17:46.306 --> 17:48.653
could this affect?

17:48.653 --> 17:50.759
- That depends.

17:52.071 --> 17:53.831
How much time did you
and Detective Dawson

17:53.831 --> 17:56.730
spend with Mr. Litvinenko?

17:56.730 --> 17:59.630
Are we talking seconds,
minutes, hours?

