[dramatic music]

19:05.351 --> 19:09.148
[alpha machine beeping]

19:09.148 --> 19:12.012
[dramatic music]

19:18.709 --> 19:20.089
- [Clive] There.

19:20.089 --> 19:21.090
Lugovoi.

19:21.090 --> 19:22.126
- Yeah, definitely.

19:24.956 --> 19:26.406
- [Clive] And these people?

19:26.406 --> 19:27.856
- They were all with him.

19:27.856 --> 19:31.342
Mr. Lugovoi booked room
441, a family suite.

19:37.866 --> 19:40.869
[cellphone beeping]

19:42.767 --> 19:44.838
[dramatic music]

19:44.838 --> 19:45.770
- Gov?

19:45.770 --> 19:46.944
- Positive reading at Itsu.

19:46.944 --> 19:48.842
- What'd you make of all this?

19:48.842 --> 19:51.604
[dramatic music]

19:51.604 --> 19:54.883
- I'm thinking, if I was
sent to assassinate someone,

19:54.883 --> 19:56.471
with the most toxic
substance in the world,

19:56.471 --> 19:58.197
would I really bring
the wife and kids?

19:58.197 --> 19:59.128
- Fair point.

19:59.128 --> 20:00.958
- Doesn't mean you stop though.

20:00.958 --> 20:03.029
And we'll read copies
of all them tapes, yes?

20:03.029 --> 20:03.857
- Yes, Gov.

20:05.549 --> 20:07.033
- And just one final question,

20:07.033 --> 20:08.724
how do I say thank
you in Italian.

20:10.416 --> 20:12.003
Oh, grazie mille, Manuela.

20:13.557 --> 20:16.836
[gentle upbeat music]

20:20.357 --> 20:21.599
- [Clive] Timmons.

20:21.599 --> 20:22.773
- We have a number
for Scaramella.

20:22.773 --> 20:24.464
I just got off the
phone with the Italians,

20:24.464 --> 20:26.052
maybe they could
nick him for us.

20:26.052 --> 20:28.503
- No one's nicking anyone Tubs.

20:28.503 --> 20:30.850
If we do that we'll need
European arrest warrants

20:30.850 --> 20:31.782
and all sorts.

20:31.782 --> 20:33.059
And by the time all that sorted,

20:33.059 --> 20:35.717
you and me will be an
home, you especially.

20:35.717 --> 20:36.994
- Yeah.

20:36.994 --> 20:37.788
- [Clive] Does he
know we're onto him?

20:37.788 --> 20:38.616
- No.

20:38.616 --> 20:39.893
- Good.

20:39.893 --> 20:41.723
Send me his number,
I'll ring him myself.

20:41.723 --> 20:42.551
- [Tubs] Where are you?

20:43.587 --> 20:45.174
- Bond Street.

20:45.174 --> 20:46.693
- You're just gonna ring him
in the middle of the street?

20:46.693 --> 20:49.282
- Tubs, this is London.

20:49.282 --> 20:52.112
The only thing
anyone's interested in
here is themselves.

20:54.460 --> 20:57.221
[car engines revving]

20:57.221 --> 21:00.500
[gentle upbeat music]

21:00.500 --> 21:01.984
[car horns honking]

21:01.984 --> 21:03.400
- [Scientist] We had positive
readings at the house,

21:03.400 --> 21:05.264
but those were secondary,
meaning Polonium wasn't present.

21:05.264 --> 21:07.231
But someone or something

21:07.231 --> 21:09.026
that had been in
contact with it was.

21:09.026 --> 21:09.854
- Litvinenko.

21:11.270 --> 21:13.582
- Which actually means, because
Polonium itself was absent,

21:13.582 --> 21:15.481
you can eliminate
the wife and son.

21:16.551 --> 21:20.348
Here though, the
readings are far higher.

21:22.660 --> 21:25.007
There was Polonium right here.

21:26.250 --> 21:30.496
[people speaking indistinctly]

21:30.496 --> 21:31.945
- He's the one who found it.

21:31.945 --> 21:33.153
- [Scientist] Yeah.

21:33.153 --> 21:34.914
- He's one of mine,
is he all right?

21:36.295 --> 21:38.573
- Well he's worried his sleeve
wasn't taped up properly.

21:38.573 --> 21:39.815
- So what next?

21:39.815 --> 21:41.334
- Well next we're getting tested

21:41.334 --> 21:44.268
and if everything's okay,
which we hope it will be,

21:44.268 --> 21:46.201
he'll be back at work
in a few days time.

21:47.375 --> 21:49.446
[people speaking indistinctly]

21:49.446 --> 21:51.068
- [Clive] And if not?

21:51.068 --> 21:52.621
- [Scientist] Jump to think.

21:52.621 --> 21:55.693
[cellphone beeping]

21:58.317 --> 22:00.146
- Mr. Scaramella.

22:00.146 --> 22:04.288
I'm calling about your late
friend, Alexander Litvinenko.

22:06.359 --> 22:08.637
No, no, it's been a real shock.

22:10.398 --> 22:12.089
No, no your English
is very good.

22:14.505 --> 22:17.128
Well, between you and
me, Mr. Scaramella,

22:17.128 --> 22:20.787
there's some individuals
we're very keen to talk to.

22:22.962 --> 22:23.894
[dramatic music]

22:23.894 --> 22:25.102
- [Pilot] Ladies and gentlemen,

22:25.102 --> 22:26.414
we're now willing to
our descent into London.

22:26.414 --> 22:29.037
[people speaking indistinctly]

22:29.037 --> 22:31.315
[dramatic music]

22:31.315 --> 22:35.319
[people speaking indistinctly]

22:48.297 --> 22:51.715
- Mr. Scaramella, I'm Detective
Chief Inspector Duncan Ball.

22:51.715 --> 22:52.509
- What?

22:53.717 --> 22:55.512
Wait, this is arrest?

22:55.512 --> 22:56.720
- This is not an arrest.

22:56.720 --> 22:58.273
- I come here for Clive Timmons.

22:58.273 --> 22:59.239
- [Duncan] We know that.

22:59.239 --> 23:00.827
- I come to help the inquiry.

23:00.827 --> 23:01.828
- And we've come to make sure

23:01.828 --> 23:03.036
that you don't change your mind.

23:04.452 --> 23:07.524
[car engine revving]

23:10.975 --> 23:14.496
[airplane engine roaring]

23:14.496 --> 23:18.293
[speaks in foreign language]

23:26.163 --> 23:28.855
[birds chirping]

23:28.855 --> 23:32.583
[speaks in foreign language]

23:35.103 --> 23:36.345
- [Anatoly] Does he stay here?

23:36.345 --> 23:37.416
- No, no, no, no,

23:37.416 --> 23:39.279
he has a house in in Ascot.

23:39.279 --> 23:42.973
But he did say he will
give you both a call, so.

23:44.319 --> 23:48.150
[speaks in foreign language]

23:50.498 --> 23:51.706
- Is it both of us, yes?

23:54.743 --> 23:57.125
[gentle music]

23:57.125 --> 23:59.783
[birds chirping]

23:59.783 --> 24:03.269
[clock ticking]

24:03.269 --> 24:05.996
[dramatic music]

