24:37.648 --> 24:38.477
[alpha machine beeping]

24:38.477 --> 24:39.892
- That makes sense.

24:39.892 --> 24:41.997
That's the table he
said they were sat at.

24:43.447 --> 24:45.553
So it's looking like he's been
poisoned at the sushi place,

24:45.553 --> 24:49.488
then walked over to the hotel,
left deposits of it there.

24:50.696 --> 24:54.493
Yeah, got 'em all, all
30 tapes ready to go.

24:54.493 --> 24:57.323
[police sirens blaring]

24:57.323 --> 24:59.567
New box set for us all to enjoy.

24:59.567 --> 25:02.190
And Lugovoi's hotel bill,

25:02.190 --> 25:04.054
including his card
and account number.

25:05.055 --> 25:06.194
- I'm not on this job.

25:06.194 --> 25:07.160
- Clive said you'd say that.

25:07.160 --> 25:08.403
And that when you did,

25:08.403 --> 25:09.991
I was to keep holding
that the piece of paper

25:09.991 --> 25:11.648
until you gave in and took it.

25:12.787 --> 25:14.513
[people speaking indistinctly]

25:14.513 --> 25:15.893
- [Reporter] In
University College

25:15.893 --> 25:18.206
and now being you
examined for radiation.

25:18.206 --> 25:21.278
The staff there tested in
case they've been exposed.

25:21.278 --> 25:23.107
Polonium-210 has been just
up on the laboratory shelf.

25:23.107 --> 25:24.108
- Thank you.

25:26.041 --> 25:28.768
- [Reporter] It's
extremely rare and exotic

25:28.768 --> 25:32.496
and an extraordinarily
potent radioactive isotope.

25:32.496 --> 25:35.188
- We know you know
about Polonium, Mario,

25:35.188 --> 25:37.225
you've mentioned it in
your intelligence reports.

25:37.225 --> 25:41.436
The question is, what
was it doing downstairs

25:41.436 --> 25:43.403
at the Itsu restaurant?

25:43.403 --> 25:46.303
Why would we find it, Mario?

25:46.303 --> 25:47.131
- Because of Sasha.

25:47.131 --> 25:48.685
- Because of Sasha.

25:48.685 --> 25:49.996
Here's one theory,

25:49.996 --> 25:51.688
you took the Polonium to Itsu

25:51.688 --> 25:53.137
because Sasha was
gonna be there.

25:53.137 --> 25:54.035
- No.

25:54.035 --> 25:55.312
- Eat there.
- No.

25:55.312 --> 25:56.520
- You arranged to
meet him at Itsu.

25:56.520 --> 25:57.763
And once you got
your food upstairs,

25:57.763 --> 26:00.766
you poisoned him in
a booth downstairs.

26:00.766 --> 26:01.870
- I come here to help you.

26:01.870 --> 26:02.837
- So help.

26:04.493 --> 26:07.496
Explain how it's possible
that you were at Itsu,

26:07.496 --> 26:10.672
Sasha was at Itsu, we
found Polonium Itsu,

26:10.672 --> 26:12.950
in the place where
you were sitting.

26:17.506 --> 26:18.611
- It was poison already.

26:18.611 --> 26:19.474
- No.
- Yes.

26:19.474 --> 26:20.855
It's the only way.

26:20.855 --> 26:22.097
- Oh really?

26:22.097 --> 26:24.237
Because prior to
meeting you that day,

26:24.237 --> 26:26.032
the day he was poisoned,

26:26.032 --> 26:28.587
the only place Sasha
had been was his house.

26:30.002 --> 26:33.281
And we found no primary
radiation there whatsoever.

26:33.281 --> 26:35.214
- Why were you so keen
to meet him for lunch?

26:35.214 --> 26:36.698
Why were you so insistent?

26:36.698 --> 26:39.805
- Because I worry
for Sasha, for me.

26:39.805 --> 26:41.910
- Because you thought
you were both targets?

26:41.910 --> 26:43.325
- Si.

26:43.325 --> 26:44.741
Sasha is my friend.

26:46.087 --> 26:47.364
He trusts me.

26:52.749 --> 26:54.405
- [Litvinenko Voiceover]
What else can I talk?

26:54.405 --> 26:56.476
Scaramella is little bit,

26:59.341 --> 27:00.446
He is madman.

27:01.689 --> 27:03.552
- [Brent] To be
clear, Scaramella

27:04.899 --> 27:06.970
might have been the
person sent to poison you?

27:08.868 --> 27:11.630
- [Litvinenko Voiceover]
It is possible.

27:11.630 --> 27:13.942
- Let's not take his
word for it, Mario,

27:15.047 --> 27:17.256
let's have you tested today.

27:17.256 --> 27:19.292
Let's have the hotel room
you staying in tested.

27:19.292 --> 27:22.399
- It's room 763 at
the Thistle Victoria.

27:22.399 --> 27:23.849
- And while we're at it,

27:23.849 --> 27:25.816
let's find out where else
you've been in London.

27:27.369 --> 27:30.407
So we gonna have those
places tested too

27:30.407 --> 27:32.892
and find out just
how possible it is.

27:34.549 --> 27:37.379
[dramatic music]

27:42.557 --> 27:45.491
- Gov, urine testing
takes at least 24 hours.

27:45.491 --> 27:47.666
Well that's what they told
Brent Hyatt and Jim Dawson.

27:47.666 --> 27:50.047
- Well, everyone else
is gonna have to wait.

27:50.047 --> 27:52.912
Oh, Mario needs to go at
the front of the queue.

27:52.912 --> 27:54.707
I'll get our team
down to his hotel.

27:56.053 --> 27:58.780
[dramatic music]

28:00.955 --> 28:04.061
[car engine revving]

28:04.061 --> 28:06.788
[dramatic music]

28:10.585 --> 28:14.727
[people speaking indistinctly]

28:14.727 --> 28:17.868
[car engine revving]

28:17.868 --> 28:20.664
[dramatic music]

28:44.136 --> 28:47.484
[alpha machine buzzing]

28:49.210 --> 28:51.730
[upbeat music]

28:51.730 --> 28:54.905
[cellphone vibrating]

28:56.735 --> 28:58.495
[people speaking indistinctly]

28:58.495 --> 29:00.048
[cellphone vibrating]

29:00.048 --> 29:02.499
- A radiation alert
is sparked in London,

29:02.499 --> 29:04.673
as it's revealed the
Russian spy was poisoned

29:04.673 --> 29:06.330
with radioactive material.

29:06.330 --> 29:09.092
- Well, she's got that
wrong for starters.

29:09.092 --> 29:10.265
He wasn't Russian, was he?

29:10.265 --> 29:12.026
He was British.

29:12.026 --> 29:14.062
- [Reporter] Are
now being monitored.

29:14.062 --> 29:16.064
Then it emerged
that it wasn't only.

29:16.064 --> 29:16.893
- Gov.

29:18.342 --> 29:19.896
Lugovoi.

29:19.896 --> 29:21.035
Here, watch.

29:22.588 --> 29:27.420
He comes from here, the Pine
Bar, and makes a call at 15:38.

29:27.420 --> 29:30.113
The clock behind reception
confirms it, look.

29:30.113 --> 29:32.080
It's the exact same time
that Sasha told Brent

29:32.080 --> 29:34.013
they spoke on the phone.

29:34.013 --> 29:35.635
The call ends.

29:35.635 --> 29:37.051
- [Clive] Kovtun.

29:37.051 --> 29:37.879
- They talk.

29:39.432 --> 29:40.261
And then

29:41.883 --> 29:42.746
the gents.

29:44.921 --> 29:45.784
- [Tubs] And?

29:47.716 --> 29:50.512
- Tubs, men don't go to
the toilets together.

29:50.512 --> 29:51.928
Well, in a nightclub maybe,

29:51.928 --> 29:54.862
but not in a hotel on
a Wednesday afternoon.

29:54.862 --> 29:56.104
[police sirens blaring]

29:56.104 --> 29:57.416
Now out comes Lugovoi,

29:59.107 --> 30:00.315
pats his pocket.

30:00.315 --> 30:02.593
- As if he's got
something in there.

30:02.593 --> 30:05.527
- [Duncan] And he's back to
the bar to wait for Litvinenko.

30:07.288 --> 30:09.462
- [Reporter] And an
extraordinarily potent.

30:10.878 --> 30:14.053
It would have to be made to
order by someone with access.

30:14.053 --> 30:16.573
- However much we'd rather
it was the Russians,

30:16.573 --> 30:17.885
over the tubby Italian.

30:18.989 --> 30:20.508
We've got Polonium in Itsu,

30:20.508 --> 30:22.579
before these boys even
enter the picture.

30:24.029 --> 30:25.754
No, and none of
this changes that.

30:26.894 --> 30:29.758
[dramatic music]

30:32.865 --> 30:34.729
- Now put it back.

30:34.729 --> 30:37.559
[dramatic music]

31:04.759 --> 31:07.866
[telephone ringing]

31:13.872 --> 31:14.700
- Timmons.

31:15.528 --> 31:18.428
[dramatic music]

31:18.428 --> 31:19.567
Tell me.

31:19.567 --> 31:22.328
[dramatic music]

31:24.572 --> 31:26.332
All right, thank you.

31:27.782 --> 31:30.509
[dramatic music]

31:51.047 --> 31:53.325
[telephones ringing]

31:53.325 --> 31:54.636
[people speaking indistinctly]

31:54.636 --> 31:55.706
[police sirens blaring]

31:55.706 --> 31:56.915
[people speaking indistinctly]

31:56.915 --> 31:59.952
[cellphone ringing]

32:01.126 --> 32:02.161
- Gov.

32:02.161 --> 32:02.955
- [Clive] Are they still going?

32:02.955 --> 32:03.783
- Just finishing up now.

32:03.783 --> 32:04.750
- Right.

32:04.750 --> 32:06.234
Go to the foyer,

32:06.234 --> 32:08.202
have them get those little
dust buster things ready

32:08.202 --> 32:09.341
and call me back, yeah.

32:10.721 --> 32:13.586
[people speaking indistinctly]

32:13.586 --> 32:15.002
[car engine revving]

32:15.002 --> 32:17.245
- [Tubs] I've got
Lugovoi's credit card bill.

32:18.902 --> 32:19.903
Interesting reading.

32:21.456 --> 32:22.871
- Scaramella's clean.

32:23.803 --> 32:27.221
His hotel room, his urine.

32:27.221 --> 32:28.670
- [Duncan] Not even secondary.

32:28.670 --> 32:31.639
- Nothing, total dead end.

32:31.639 --> 32:33.434
- Clive, forget Scaramella.

32:35.539 --> 32:37.714
Right, according to this,

32:37.714 --> 32:39.233
Lugovoi has used the
same card for everything.

32:39.233 --> 32:41.200
He's paid the hotel bill,
the one Deborah gave me,

32:41.200 --> 32:44.100
he's done shopping, bars,

32:44.100 --> 32:47.103
and he's also used it on a trip
to London two weeks earlier

32:47.103 --> 32:51.176
and on the 16th of
October on Piccadilly.

32:52.349 --> 32:54.558
He's used it to
buy food from Itsu.

32:54.558 --> 32:56.871
[dramatic music]

32:56.871 --> 32:58.459
- It's definitely
two weeks prior

32:58.459 --> 33:00.288
and it's definitely
the right Itsu?

33:00.288 --> 33:01.496
- Yeah.

33:01.496 --> 33:04.568
[cellphone ringing]

33:06.432 --> 33:07.606
- You in the foyer?

33:07.606 --> 33:08.745
- Yes, Gov.

33:08.745 --> 33:10.126
- [Clive] Right.

33:10.126 --> 33:13.094
Stand in the middle by
yourself, facing the entrance.

33:13.094 --> 33:15.579
Now that's 12 o'clock,
turn to your left

33:16.442 --> 33:17.788
and face to 10.

33:17.788 --> 33:19.100
You see a door?

33:19.100 --> 33:20.308
- Yes, Gov.

33:20.308 --> 33:21.240
- Right, that's a gents.

33:21.240 --> 33:23.380
Tell them to check in the gents.

33:23.380 --> 33:25.382
[dramatic music]

33:25.382 --> 33:27.902
What is it about Itsu
they like so much.

33:27.902 --> 33:29.283
- That's just it,
Gov, it's not them,

33:29.283 --> 33:31.354
it's Litvinenko, it's
where he liked to meet.

33:31.354 --> 33:34.667
- So if they were there,
they were there to meet him.

33:34.667 --> 33:37.429
[dramatic music]

33:59.002 --> 34:01.729
[dramatic music]

34:02.868 --> 34:06.147
[alpha machine buzzing]

34:08.494 --> 34:11.221
[dramatic music]

34:16.054 --> 34:19.643
[alpha machine buzzing]

34:19.643 --> 34:21.300
[dramatic music]

34:21.300 --> 34:22.991
[cellphone ringing]

34:22.991 --> 34:24.165
- Yep.

34:24.165 --> 34:25.787
- [Deborah] They're
saying it's FSD.

34:25.787 --> 34:26.685
- Meaning?

34:26.685 --> 34:27.893
- Full Scale Deflection.

34:27.893 --> 34:30.378
Apparently that's as
radioactive as it gets.

34:30.378 --> 34:32.035
- That's it.

34:32.035 --> 34:32.863
Thank you.

34:37.799 --> 34:39.284
Right.

34:39.284 --> 34:40.319
Ladies and gentlemen,

34:41.803 --> 34:44.944
these are our boys.

34:47.464 --> 34:49.190
They come over,

34:49.190 --> 34:52.193
they meet Sasha at Itsu

34:52.193 --> 34:53.781
and they try to whack him there.

34:53.781 --> 34:54.678
- But they fail.

34:54.678 --> 34:55.610
- Yes.

34:55.610 --> 34:58.165
But that explains our findings.

34:58.165 --> 35:02.169
Two weeks later,
they come back again,

35:02.169 --> 35:04.205
only this time they bring
their families with them

35:04.205 --> 35:06.207
so as not to seem
too suspicious.

35:07.657 --> 35:11.971
However, this time they
want him to come to them,

35:13.180 --> 35:17.425
to do it on their turf,
on on their terms.

35:17.425 --> 35:19.565
So as they won't screw
it up a second time.

35:21.395 --> 35:22.534
But when he gets there.

35:22.534 --> 35:24.087
- [Duncan] Gov.

35:24.087 --> 35:26.917
[dramatic music]

35:32.130 --> 35:34.062
- When he gets there,
they're waiting.

35:35.512 --> 35:40.241
They have the poison, they
have the CCTV blind spot.

35:41.449 --> 35:43.451
They've even ordered
a pot of green tea.

35:45.246 --> 35:50.251
All they need now is for
Sasha Litvinenko to turn up,

35:52.288 --> 35:53.151
sit down.

35:57.085 --> 35:57.914
And take a sip.

35:58.811 --> 36:01.573
[dramatic music]

36:03.299 --> 36:05.715
[bells ringing]

36:05.715 --> 36:09.063
[wind gushing]

36:09.063 --> 36:10.375
- I thought it might
be worth giving you

36:10.375 --> 36:12.031
the Russian angle on this.

36:13.447 --> 36:16.277
If a Russian citizen is deemed
to be an enemy of the state,

36:16.277 --> 36:18.866
then no matter where in
the world he happens to be,

36:18.866 --> 36:22.525
he is under their rules,
at least fair game.

36:22.525 --> 36:23.802
- That's not what this is.

36:23.802 --> 36:26.667
- Litvinenko had been
stirring things up.

36:26.667 --> 36:28.013
Before Putin even got in,

36:28.013 --> 36:30.153
he'd as good as branded
him a war criminal.

36:31.844 --> 36:34.813
He had also been doing some
work for us, between you and me.

36:34.813 --> 36:36.987
So I don't wanna say the
man was asking for trouble.

36:36.987 --> 36:37.954
- That system

36:37.954 --> 36:39.197
doesn't apply.
- But he was

36:39.197 --> 36:40.922
asking for trouble.
- Because Litvinenko

36:40.922 --> 36:42.130
wasn't Russian.

36:42.130 --> 36:43.028
- He was KGB.

36:43.028 --> 36:43.822
- [Peter] Ex.

36:43.822 --> 36:44.754
- No such thing.

36:44.754 --> 36:45.720
- And a citizen of this country.

36:45.720 --> 36:47.205
- For about five minutes.

36:47.205 --> 36:48.482
There's stuff in my fridge

36:48.482 --> 36:50.863
that's been British
longer than he has.

36:50.863 --> 36:53.418
- If we don't draw the line
here, it's open season.

36:54.626 --> 36:56.214
Anyone from any country

36:56.214 --> 36:58.319
can do their dirty
work on our patch.

36:58.319 --> 37:01.633
He lived here, had
his family here.

37:01.633 --> 37:03.462
He also, in case
you'd forgotten,

37:03.462 --> 37:05.844
did a fair amount
of work for you.

37:05.844 --> 37:07.363
So he must be protected

37:07.363 --> 37:09.261
under the laws of
the United Kingdom.

37:11.367 --> 37:12.230
Surely.

37:15.336 --> 37:17.580
- How about we start
this conversation again?

37:20.445 --> 37:24.276
[speaks in foreign language]

37:26.105 --> 37:27.314
- Mom.

37:27.314 --> 37:28.522
- [Translator] There
was no indication

37:28.522 --> 37:29.868
it was a violent
death in the report.

37:29.868 --> 37:31.110
- Mom.

37:31.110 --> 37:31.835
- [Translator] By
British doctors.

37:31.835 --> 37:33.216
It's not there.

37:33.216 --> 37:37.047
[speaks in foreign language]

37:38.359 --> 37:39.602
- [Translator] For Litvinenko,

37:39.602 --> 37:40.844
then why was it not
published earlier?

37:40.844 --> 37:42.260
If it was written
after his death,

37:42.260 --> 37:44.262
then there is no
need to comment.

37:44.262 --> 37:45.401
[speaks in foreign language]

37:45.401 --> 37:48.369
We knew that Litvinenko
is not Lazarus.

37:48.369 --> 37:52.270
[speaks in foreign language]

37:52.270 --> 37:54.824
[gentle music]

37:58.310 --> 38:02.452
[speaks in foreign language]

38:02.452 --> 38:05.075
[gentle music]

38:11.254 --> 38:12.255
- Putin.

38:12.255 --> 38:15.983
[speaks in foreign language]

38:20.988 --> 38:23.818
[dramatic music]

38:25.924 --> 38:28.167
- Andrei Lugovoi
and Dmitry Kovtun

38:28.167 --> 38:30.929
flew back to Russia on
the 3rd of November.

38:30.929 --> 38:33.621
It is not enough to know
that these are our men.

38:33.621 --> 38:37.107
What we have to do now is
secure physical evidence

38:37.107 --> 38:40.973
that links them and only
them to the Polonium.

38:42.389 --> 38:44.908
- The readings from the Pine
Bar are pretty conclusive.

38:44.908 --> 38:48.256
- But where did they
go that Sasha didn't.

38:48.256 --> 38:51.605
- Lugovoi went to a match,
Arsenal versus CSK Moscow.

38:51.605 --> 38:53.123
That was the night of the first.

38:53.123 --> 38:56.092
- Yeah, they ate in a place
called Pescatore, night after.

38:56.092 --> 38:57.265
- We'll have those
checked today.

38:57.265 --> 38:58.232
- And you should.

38:58.232 --> 38:59.716
But for us,

38:59.716 --> 39:03.513
anything that comes after they
met Litvinenko doesn't work

39:03.513 --> 39:06.378
because the radiation could
still have come from him.

39:06.378 --> 39:08.553
So, where were they before?

39:08.553 --> 39:11.349
That's what we need
to make this stick.

39:12.350 --> 39:15.525
[telephones ringing]

39:17.078 --> 39:19.771
- What about the
airplane they came in on?

39:19.771 --> 39:22.049
It's not as if they
could deny being on that.

39:23.602 --> 39:25.155
- Thank you.

39:25.155 --> 39:26.847
That's it.

39:26.847 --> 39:29.436
That becomes our top priority.

39:29.436 --> 39:30.298
Good work.

39:31.576 --> 39:35.649
[people speaking indistinctly]

39:35.649 --> 39:37.892
- [Reporter] In a statement
made earlier today,

39:37.892 --> 39:40.481
President Putin played
down any suggestion

39:40.481 --> 39:41.862
of Russian involvement.

39:41.862 --> 39:42.725
Also passing doubt.

39:42.725 --> 39:45.003
[cellphone ringing]

39:45.003 --> 39:46.211
- Hello.

39:46.211 --> 39:48.006
- [Dr. Onome] Detective Hyatt.

39:48.006 --> 39:48.938
- Speaking.

39:48.938 --> 39:50.836
- This is Dr. Onome George,

39:50.836 --> 39:53.183
calling from Public
Health England.

39:53.183 --> 39:54.668
I have some results for you.

39:55.841 --> 39:58.326
I'm pleased to inform
you that your sample

39:58.326 --> 39:59.983
has come back negative.

39:59.983 --> 40:02.158
[sighing]

40:03.331 --> 40:05.748
- And Jim Dawson, my colleague?

40:05.748 --> 40:06.956
- [Dr. Onome] I'm afraid

40:06.956 --> 40:09.199
I can't really go
into details on that.

40:09.199 --> 40:10.408
- Of course.

40:10.408 --> 40:13.065
- Though, I can tell
you I'm about to make

40:13.065 --> 40:16.448
a very similar call to Detective
Dawson in just one second.

40:16.448 --> 40:17.311
[gentle music]

40:17.311 --> 40:19.313
[laughing]

40:19.313 --> 40:20.279
- Thank you.

40:20.279 --> 40:21.867
- [Dr. Onome] Okay.

40:22.834 --> 40:24.560
- Yeah, thank you.

40:24.560 --> 40:25.526
- [Dr. Onome] You take care now.

40:25.526 --> 40:26.596
- Okay, bye.

40:26.596 --> 40:28.322
- [Dr. Onome] Bye-Bye.

40:28.322 --> 40:30.911
[gentle music]

40:34.328 --> 40:36.641
[laughing]

40:39.885 --> 40:41.439
- I'm heading in.

40:41.439 --> 40:44.027
- You want me to leave
something in the fridge tonight?

40:44.027 --> 40:45.857
- No, let's eat together.

40:45.857 --> 40:47.721
[gentle music]

40:47.721 --> 40:49.550
It's a good night
for an early night.

40:50.551 --> 40:53.209
[gentle music]

41:00.906 --> 41:04.738
- Okay, BA 873 is the
one they flew in on.

41:04.738 --> 41:07.465
Seats 23C and 23D.

41:07.465 --> 41:08.466
- Right.

41:08.466 --> 41:10.122
Where is it now?

41:10.122 --> 41:11.883
- Well, it's changed
flight number of course.

41:11.883 --> 41:14.817
But the plane itself with
that registration mark

41:14.817 --> 41:19.235
is currently
Heathrow, Terminal 2.

41:20.719 --> 41:22.514
- You mean it's here, right now.

41:23.826 --> 41:24.758
[dramatic music]

41:24.758 --> 41:27.243
[airplane engine roaring]

41:27.243 --> 41:30.798
[dramatic music]

41:30.798 --> 41:34.595
[alpha machine buzzing]

41:34.595 --> 41:37.356
[dramatic music]

41:42.741 --> 41:46.193
[alpha machine beeping]

41:46.193 --> 41:48.885
[dramatic music]

41:51.474 --> 41:53.580
[camera shutter clicking]

41:53.580 --> 41:56.410
[dramatic music]

42:05.108 --> 42:07.939
- Confirm contamination
on seat 23D.

42:07.939 --> 42:08.767
- 23D was.

42:09.906 --> 42:11.529
- Lugovoi.

42:11.529 --> 42:14.117
[telephone ringing]

42:14.117 --> 42:16.741
[dramatic music]

42:16.741 --> 42:18.294
- Gov.

42:18.294 --> 42:19.122
We've got it.

42:20.020 --> 42:21.090
Clear evidence.

42:21.090 --> 42:23.057
It was Lugovoi and Kovtun.

42:23.057 --> 42:24.990
They came to the
country fully loaded.

42:24.990 --> 42:27.614
It's enough, in my opinion,
to apply for extradition.

42:28.684 --> 42:30.271
Do I make the
application or do you?

42:30.271 --> 42:31.203
- Clive.

42:31.203 --> 42:32.480
- I think it should be you

42:32.480 --> 42:33.723
because it'll carry
more weight when it.

42:33.723 --> 42:36.070
- Clive, there'll
be no application.

42:36.070 --> 42:37.071
There's resistance.

42:37.934 --> 42:38.763
- Resistance from who?

42:38.763 --> 42:39.764
- You saw the news.

42:39.764 --> 42:40.765
- Resistance from who?

42:40.765 --> 42:42.490
- At this level,
it's not just us

42:42.490 --> 42:43.733
who need to decide
on these things.

42:43.733 --> 42:45.010
- But we need to
talk to these men.

42:45.010 --> 42:46.149
- I agree.

42:46.149 --> 42:46.943
- Interview them.
- Ideally.

42:46.943 --> 42:47.875
But on this occasion,

42:47.875 --> 42:49.118
we may have to limit ourselves

42:49.118 --> 42:51.189
to correctly identifying
the culprits.

42:51.189 --> 42:53.122
- That's not good enough.

42:53.122 --> 42:55.055
That's not the promise
we made to Marina.

42:55.055 --> 42:56.056
- That's the reality.

42:58.299 --> 43:00.439
[clock ticking]

43:00.439 --> 43:02.131
- Answer me this.

43:02.131 --> 43:04.651
Are they saying we
can't speak to these men

43:04.651 --> 43:06.756
or just that we
can't extradite them?

43:06.756 --> 43:07.585
Which is it, Sir?

43:10.277 --> 43:12.520
- There is no
extradition agreement

43:12.520 --> 43:15.213
between the UK and Russia.

43:15.213 --> 43:16.490
- Well, that's just something

43:16.490 --> 43:17.664
we'll have to work
around, isn't it?

43:21.840 --> 43:23.808
[telephone ringing]

43:23.808 --> 43:26.569
[dramatic music]

43:27.535 --> 43:29.572
[telephones ringing]

43:29.572 --> 43:32.782
[gentle upbeat music]

43:48.073 --> 43:49.419
- Where's Tubs?

43:49.419 --> 43:50.282
- In the gents Gov.

43:50.282 --> 43:51.111
- Is he now?

43:52.146 --> 43:55.494
[gentle upbeat music]

44:08.473 --> 44:10.475
- I thought we agreed men don't
go to the toilets together

44:10.475 --> 44:12.028
in the middle of the afternoon.

44:15.342 --> 44:20.036
- Tubs, I need you
to go to Moscow.

44:26.422 --> 44:29.011
[gentle music]

44:31.013 --> 44:34.223
[birds chirping]

44:34.223 --> 44:36.915
[gentle music]

44:36.915 --> 44:39.677
- [Aiden] Very kind
of you, young man.

44:39.677 --> 44:41.679
[gentle music]

44:41.679 --> 44:45.234
[birds chirping]

44:45.234 --> 44:48.340
[telephone ringing]

44:50.653 --> 44:51.481
- Hello.

44:51.481 --> 44:52.413
- [Caller] Marina.

44:52.413 --> 44:53.518
- Boris?

44:53.518 --> 44:57.280
[speaks in foreign language]

45:10.121 --> 45:11.053
[dramatic music]

45:11.053 --> 45:13.262
[speaks in foreign language]

45:13.262 --> 45:15.471
[gasping]

45:15.471 --> 45:18.198
[dramatic music]

45:20.165 --> 45:20.994
- Anatoly.

45:21.822 --> 45:22.961
[dramatic music]

45:22.961 --> 45:25.205
[shouting]

45:26.724 --> 45:28.864
[gasping]

45:33.178 --> 45:36.009
[dramatic music]

45:45.708 --> 45:48.469
[dramatic music]

45:56.132 --> 45:58.859
[dramatic music]
